Story Title: As a user I want a textbox I can type in keywords to search
As a user, I want the navigation bar that I can easily find
As a user, I want to be able to sort the authors by their last name, their first name, their number of books, the overall rating of their books and those who have new releases
As a developer I want to see how search has been implemented on this website for getting hints
As a user, I want to be able to sort the books by rating, the alphabet, and published date
As a user after searching results, I want to be able to click on results after searching
As a user I want pagination provided for search results for easier navigation through the results
As a user, I want to be able to be able to filter the books, authors, reviews, and series that I can see.
As a website user if I search for a keyword and an unexpected result pops up, I'd like to see the keyword highlighted with its context to see why that result popped up
As a user, I want to be able to search for a keyword within the site.
As a developer or a professor, I would like to see technical documentation so that I can see what the web developers use to create their website
As a visitor to the website, I should be able to visit a page that allows me to view all of the reviews
As someone who reads through all books very quickly, I would love to easily be able to see new releases.
As someone visiting the website, I should be able to visit a page that allows me to search through all of the authors

As a book reader, whenever I look for a series of books, I want to be able to look to see if it's ongoing so that I can pull an all-nighter and not be left hanging. I would also like to see the author and reviews on the series.
As a reader with limited free time, I would like to see if a book is part of a series and if so, how long that series is.
As someone visiting the website, I should be able to visit a page that allows me to see all of the series
As a book reader looking for new books I want to see the information listed out for me so I can learn more about the book's backstory
As a fan of specific authors, I would like to visit their page and learn about them to see how their life could've influenced their novels.
as a user I need to see who built this very cool website so that can learn about a bunch of awesome people
developers should be able to read how we hosted our website so that they can host their own website
As a book reader, I want to be able to view the series of a book so I am not left with a cliffhanger. I need closure
developers should be able to read what tools we used so that they can implement their own website
As a user, I want to view a beautiful homepage and a carousel so that I can be drawn to use the website
As an author, I would like to be able to visit my page and see all the wonderful reviews about the books I have written
As a budding developer, I would like to have the API available to me so that I can scrape the API and use it to make a better website
As someone visiting the webpage I want to be given interesting info on the front page, such as highly rated authors/books so visiting the website introduced me to new things.
As a book reader, I would like to be able to choose a book and look at the reviews so I can see other's people opinions on the book
As someone visiting the website when I click on a book on a grid page, I want to be able to return to my place in the grid when I'm done looking at the book
users should be able to see what sources we used to scrape our data so that they can use them in case they need it :)
As someone visiting the website I should be able to go to a page that allows me to go through all of the books, so I can see all the wonderful books to read.
series model page: grid of book cover of the first book and silhouette to show series
Instance series page - carousel of book covers, bottom right pic of author
Instance review page - book cover picture (left), review (right)
Instance author page- author picture in the left, book covers along the bottom, other attributes on the right
About Page- all the stuff
Instance Book page - one large cover on the left. To the right of it have the most important information. Reviews underneath it.
Have a home page with a carousel of award winning books. On the top there is a navigation bar and search bar. Display relevant information, reviews, tweets, or articles.
